(y^2-xy)dx+x^2dy=0
(y^2 - xy)dx + x^2dy = 0
(xy - y^2)dx = x^2dy
\begin{align}\frac{dy}{dx} &= \frac{xy - y^2}{x^2}\\ &= \frac{y}{x} - \left(\frac{y}{x}\right)^2\end{align}
v = \frac{y}{x} \implies y = vx \implies \frac{dy}{dx} = v + x\frac{dv}{dx}
x
C
v = \frac{y}{x}
v + x\frac{dv}{dx} = v - v^2
x\frac{dv}{dx} = -v^2
\frac{1}{v^2}\frac{dv}{dx} = -\frac{1}{x}
\int\frac{1}{v^2}\frac{dv}{dx}\cdot dx = \int\frac{-1}{x}dx
\int\frac{1}{v^2}dv = \int\frac{-1}{x}dx
-v^{-1} = -\ln{|x|} - C
v^{-1} = \ln{|x|} + C
v = \frac{1}{\ln{|x|} + C}
\frac{y}{x} = \frac{1}{\ln{|x|} + C}
y = \frac{x}{\ln{|x|} + C}
